being 7 years older than my sister meant I was always more of a third parent than a sibling. I knew how to protect, guide, “be responsible”… but I didn’t know how to just be.. 

Today, I’m 25 and she’s 18… and somehow she became my best friend, my secret-keeper, my voice of reason, and the one person who just gets me without needing an explanation 💞✨🎀 

I was told she was meant to be there for me one day, but no one told me she’d be this extraordinary⭐️ I find myself leaning on her more than I ever imagined, laughing with her about everything, crying to her about nothing, and realizing that age really has nothing on the kind of love we share 🌸🤍

I’m still the cool older sister (obviously), but more than that, I’m just so lucky to call her my younger sister 💘 
.
.
